This paper discusses privacy guarantees in data analysis, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper focuses on differential privacy, a popular privacy model in the security community. The paper also discusses data distortion and analytical accuracy, which are topics that fall under cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new privacy notion that allows for adjusting the level of protection to the actual data set, which involves information theory and falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of privacy guarantees on data controllers, which falls under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
